From 83eb814fc4d21d34abc2df9ba218363fa309976e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: HackerAI <hackerai@danatrap.local>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 02:07:37 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: audio seek via ?start= param + VTT overlay subtitles
 (bypass <track> unreliability)

Backend:
- Added ?start=<seconds> query param to /audio endpoint
- ffmpeg -ss input seeking for fast audio seek support

Frontend:
- Audio: use ?start=currentTime in audio URL instead of a.currentTime=v.currentTime
  (streamed MP4 has no Range support, currentTime seeking fails silently)
- Audio: on video seek, reload audio with new ?start= param
- Audio: remove all currentTime syncing from _syncAudioToVideo and _onAudioCanPlay
- Subtitles: replace <track> DOM approach with direct VTT fetch + parse
- Subtitles: render as overlay div via sc-if, updated on timeupdate
- Subtitles: _parseVTT extracts cues, _updateSubtitle finds active cue
- Synced android-app/www/index.html
